<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-07T06:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-07T06:35:00-05:00" n="366" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.91/9–744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-07T15:00:00+03:25">September 7, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 5:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>671. ReDepts 526 August 23. On the occasion of presentation of my
                                credentials the Shah expressed himself as displeased at the failure
                                of the United States to sign the troop agreement. I said I
                                understood it was the Iranian Government which was delaying
                                signature and the Prime Minister intervened to say the matter was
                                receiving attention and he hoped to send new proposals to Washington
                                by the recently appointed Iranian Ambassador. Before doing so he
                                said he wished to have a conference on the question with the
                                Ambassador and me.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>